Response ID: resp_2488
Response Text: In my NW Austin neighborhood, it feels suburban and far removed from the culture that is offered downtown. We have the very commercial Domain area, but it would be great to have some culture available along the 183 corridor. Selfishly, I would like it near 183 and Duval, but I think it would be great to actually bring some art and culture to 183 and Ohlen Road. The north central area of Austin is so down-trodden and sad, it would be nice to lift that community and give those local residents the opportunity to experience art and culture in their area. I never visit the Doughtery Arts Center because of the location -- if we had a version of that in North Austin, I would be very active in taking classes. I'd be happy to volunteer there as well. Traffic and lack of parking make it difficult for me to be motivated to go downtown. I would imagine others share the lack of enthusiasm for going downtown or even crossing the river to go to events because of traffic and parking issues.

